Template: rpiap/wlanssid
Type: string
Default: rpiap
Description: Enter SSID:
 Enter the name (SSID) of your wireless network (WLAN).

Template: rpiap/wlanpassword
Type: password
Description: Enter password:
 Set a WPA password for your WLAN.
 The password must be at least 8 characters long.
 If you are reconfiguring the package, leaving this field blank will keep the
 current password unchanged.

Template: rpiap/wlanchannel
Type: string
Default: 6
Description: Enter WLAN channel:
 Choose a WLAN channel if you want to use a specific one.
 For 2.4 GHz, recommended channels are 1, 6, or 11.
 For 5 GHz, you can use 36, 40, 44, or 48.
 If you are not sure, just keep the default (6).

Template: rpiap/wlancountry
Type: string
Default: CZ
Description: Enter WLAN country code:
 Country code (ISO/IEC 3166-1) used to set the regulatory domain.
 This may limit available channels and transmit power.
 Default: CZ

Template: rpiap/dhcpdns
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Use DNS server from DHCP?
 If you need to use local DNS resolvers, for example to resolve internal DNS
 zones, select 'Yes'. To use the internal DNS server and benefit from support
 for encrypted DNS (DNSCurve), leave the default setting as 'No'.

Template: rpiap/mode
Type: select
Default: ap
Choices: ap, client, custom
Description: Select operating mode:
 Choose the operating mode for your setup.
 .
 ap - Access Point mode (default):
     WiFi interface acts as an access point, providing a wireless LAN network
     for client devices to connect. Ethernet interface or plug-and-play USB
     devices (like mobile phones with tethering) can be used for WAN connection
     to the internet. This is the standard home router configuration.
 .
 client - Wireless Client mode:
     Ethernet interface provides wired LAN for client devices, while WiFi
     interface connects to an external wireless network as WAN. Other interfaces
     can be used as optional WAN connections if needed.
 .
 custom - Custom mode:
     Select your own combination of LAN interfaces (for experts only).

Template: rpiap/laninterfaces
Type: multiselect
Choices: wlan0, eth0, eth1, eth2, usb0
Default: wlan0
Description: Select LAN interfaces:
 This is an advanced option for experts only. Interfaces you select here
 will be part of your LAN bridge, providing network access to client
 devices.
 .
 All other available interfaces (those not selected here) will be automatically
 used as WAN connections if connected. This includes additional USB network
 adapters, mobile phones with tethering, etc.).
 .
 This option is only shown when "custom" mode is selected.
 .
 Available interfaces:
  - wlan0: Raspberry PI wireless interface
  - eth0: Raspberry PI ethernet interface
  - eth1, eth2, usb0: additional plug-and-play USB network interfaces

Template: rpiap/restart
Type: text
Description: Restart services.
 To apply the changes, the services must be restarted. Please restart them
 manually using: "svc -t /etc/service/rpiap_*". Note that if you are connected
 via SSH, the restart may terminate the connection.
 Alternatively, performing a system reboot will restart all services and apply
 the changes as well.

